name: Snoopy vs. the Red Baron
comments: #1 for five weeks in Australia, #2 on the US Hot 100 during the week of December 31, 1966 (behind the Monkees' "I'm a Believer"), #4 in The Netherlands and #8 in the UK. While waiting for clearance on the use of the "Snoopy" name, ""queaky vs. The Black Knight"" was released in Canada in a new recording with the names changed. Rights were indeed obtained and the original "Snoopy Vs. the Red Baron" title was used.
